        <div class="tab-pane" id="submissions" role="tabpanel">
          <h5>By submitting, you agree to follow these rules:</h5>
          <p>
          <ul class="smallList">
            <li><i>TIME REQUIREMENT</i> - All submissions are expected to represent at least 30 minutes of concentrated effort on the submission as a whole
              or as far as progress is made on the work.
            </li>
            <li><i>NO WORKING AHEAD</i> - Your submission, or the progress represented on said submission, must have been made within one day of your submission period.</li>
            <li><i>OWNERSHIP</i> - Any image you upload must represent your own work.</li>
            <li><i>WIPS PERMITTED</i> - It's ok to submit the same piece in succession over multiple days if each subsequent submission represents
              sufficient additional time being spent on the piece as it comes together.
            </li>
            <li><i>CHALLENGES</i> - When attaching a submission to a challenge, double check to see if it meets the criteria for the challenge. For example, some challenges
              require you to submit completed pieces only, others permit sketches, WIPS and so on.
            </li>
            <li><i>OBJECTIONABLE CONTENT</i> - Please use tact in what you create. Erotic depictions of what appear to be minors, works that reflect extreme or hateful ideologies,
              or direct attacks on other members of the website may be removed and the creators warned or reprimanded.
            </li>
            <li><i>NOT A GALLERY</i> - DAD is geared towards the documentation and formation of your drawing habits. This is not a place to display every art piece you've ever made, or
              commemorate another artist.
            </li>
            <li><i>NO ILLEGAL CONTENT</i> - Speaks for itself. Neither your description nor the image itself should contain any illicit content.</li>
          </ul>
          </p>
          <br>
          <h5>Editing and Deleting</h5>
          <p>On the day of submission, you may edit any aspect of your submission, or delete it in its entirety.
             However, be wary! The day after a submission is made (i.e., after rollover), <i>you may no longer
             delete said submission, and editing will be heavily limited.</i> The reason for this is to prevent
             certain abuse cases. For instance, people submitting garbage images and replacing them with their
             actual work after the deadline, in an effort to extend their deadline. Thorough purges of all your 
             work can be requested by reaching out to the DAD admins.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane" id="comments" role="tabpanel">
          <h5>By commenting, you agree to follow these rules:</h5>
          <p>
            <b>Mandatory</b>
            <ul class="smallList">
              <li><i>NO SELF PROMOTION</i> - Comments are not your place to promote your own work.</li>
              <li><i>NO BULLYING</i> - Criticism is one thing, but hateful, vindictive or purposefully offensive comments will not be tolerated.</li>
              <li><i>NO ADVERTISING</i> - Using comment space to promote a website, product or service is unacceptable.</li>
              <li><i>NO SPAMMING</i> - Do not spam the comments section, or post completely irrelevant text. Filling the remainder of your comment with garbage text for the sake of hitting the character prerequisite is also not permitted.</li>
              <li><i>NO BEGGING</i> - Do not use comment space to request work, or highly customized adjustments from the artist.</li>
              <li><i>NO PIRATING</i> - Sharing is caring, but not here. Please keep links to your torrents, rips and MEGAs outside of DAD.</li>
              <li><i>NO COMPRESSED LINKS</i> - Even if you don't intend anything malicious, please avoid using url shorteners.</li>
              <li><i>NO ILLEGAL CONTENT</i> - Speaks for itself.</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
          <p>
            <b>Recommended</b>
            <ul class="smallList">
              <li><i>COMPLIMENTS</i> - People love receiving compliments. Take your feedback a little further by pointing out specific aspects of the drawing that were effective, or toss in a word of encouragement!</li>
              <li><i>CRITICISM</i> - Criticism is at its most useful when it is given as objectively and detailed as possible. Make sure your points serve as useful direction or actionable tasks for the recipient to achieve.</li>
              <li><i>PERSONAL PREFERENCES</i> - Art is highly subjective, but do your best to distinguish between what are objective issues and what are your personal preferences.</li>
              <li><i>LINKING</i> - Links are a mixed bag. Please abstain from explicitly promoting products, and try to pass useful free references and materials if possible. Don't hesitate, however, to link to a redline you've made, or a directly applicable tutorial, video or resource.</li>
              <li><i>RESPONSES</i> - Nobody's perfect. Please try to stay receptive to constructive criticism.</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
